Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Trim the @courgette{1}, then quarter lengthways. Chop widthways into small pieces.

Drain and rinse the @mixed beans{1%400g can} in a #sieve{}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat.

Once hot, add the pepper and courgette. Stir-fry until softened, ~{5-6%minutes}, then add the garlic and @Mexican style spice mix{1} (add less if you'd prefer things milder). Cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Stir in the mixed beans, @chopped tomatoes with onion and garlic{1}(finely chopped) and @vegetable stock paste{1%tsp}, then simmer until the liquid has reduced by half, ~{10-12%minutes}. Add a splash of water if it gets too thick.

While the beans and veg simmer, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g} and halve the @lime{1/2}.

Lay the @plain taco tortillas{4} (2 per person) onto a large #baking tray{} in a single layer and rub each with a little @oil{}.

Season with @salt{}, then bake on the top shelf of the oven until golden and crispy, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> Tostada means 'toasted', so make sure they're crispy!

Meanwhile, halve the @avocado{1} and remove the stone. Use a #tablespoon{} to scoop the flesh out into a #bowl{}.

Add a squeeze of lime juice to the avocado and mash together with a #fork{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then set your guacamole aside.

When everything's ready, taste and season the beans with salt and pepper if needed.

Pop the tostadas onto your plates and top with the bean mixture and guacamole - as much as you'd like.

Sprinkle over the cheese to finish.

> Tostadas are best enjoyed eaten by hand - get stuck in! Enjoy!